exports[`Directions tab golden > matches snapshot for Day 2 fixture 1`] = `"<div class="directions"><h3>Leg 1: Windhoek, Namibia → Solitaire, Namibia</h3><p><strong>187 km</strong> · <strong>2 hours 45 mins</strong></p><ol><li class="step step-heather-maybe"><span class="step-dir" title="Direction of travel">⬅️</span> Head west on Independence Ave <small>1 km · 2 mins</small> <span class="step-heather-chip step-heather-chip-maybe" title="B1 paved trunk highway for the first ~90 km is comfortable. Hand the wheel at or before Rehoboth — the C24 gravel + Spreetshoogte Pass (14% gradient, 1,000 m drop in 4 km, no guardrails) is firmly David-only.">🟡 Heather: B1 Windhoek → Rehoboth only</span> <button class="step-expand" data-leg="0" data-step="0" aria-label="Expand step on map">🗺️</button><details class="step-conditions"> <summary class="step-conditions-summary"> <span class="step-road-pill">mixed</span> <span class="step-conditions-toggle">conditions ▾</span> </summary> <div class="step-conditions-body"> <div class="step-road"><strong>Road:</strong> Mixed local roads — surface and conditions vary segment to segment.</div> <div class="step-rain"><strong>Rain:</strong> Rain: check the worst surface type on this leg before deciding. Local advice from the lodge or Solitaire stop is the best signal.</div> <div class="step-why"><strong>Heather rating:</strong> Heather maybe — conditional on conditions matching the plan; David should monitor and be ready to swap. (Source note: B1 paved trunk highway for the first ~90 km is comfortable. Hand the wheel at or before Rehoboth — the C24 gravel + Spreetshoogte Pass (14% gradient, 1,000 m drop in 4 km, no guardrails) is firmly David-only.)</div> </div></details><div class="step-media"> <div class="step-map-osm" data-leg="0" data-step="0" data-status="maybe"></div> <img class="step-streetview" loading="lazy" src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mNkYAAAAAYAAjCB0C8AAAAASUVORK5CYII=" alt="Street view at step 1"> </div></li><li class="step step-heather-maybe"><span class="step-dir" title="Direction of travel">⬅️</span> Turn left onto B1 toward Rehoboth <small>85 km · 1 hour 5 mins</small> <span class="step-heather-chip step-heather-chip-maybe" title="B1 paved trunk highway for the first ~90 km is comfortable. Hand the wheel at or before Rehoboth — the C24 gravel + Spreetshoogte Pass (14% gradient, 1,000 m drop in 4 km, no guardrails) is firmly David-only.">🟡 Heather: B1 Windhoek → Rehoboth only</span> <button class="step-expand" data-leg="0" data-step="1" aria-label="Expand step on map">🗺️</button><details class="step-conditions"> <summary class="step-conditions-summary"> <span class="step-road-pill">B1</span> <span class="step-conditions-toggle">conditions ▾</span> </summary> <div class="step-conditions-body"> <div class="step-road"><strong>Road:</strong> Bituminous (paved) road. Smooth surface, standard rules apply. Typical legal limit 100–120 km/h on open paved roads.</div> <div class="step-rain"><strong>Rain:</strong> Rain: minor impact. Watch for aquaplaning at speed and oil-slicks after a dry spell. Visibility drops sharply in heavy downpours — slow down and turn on lights.</div> <div class="step-why"><strong>Heather rating:</strong> Heather maybe — surface is paved, but conditional on traffic/signage clarity and that she feels rested. David should take over if anything feels off. (Source note: B1 paved trunk highway for the first ~90 km is comfortable. Hand the wheel at or before Rehoboth — the C24 gravel + Spreetshoogte Pass (14% gradient, 1,000 m drop in 4 km, no guardrails) is firmly David-only.)</div> </div></details><div class="step-media"> <div class="step-map-osm" data-leg="0" data-step="1" data-status="maybe"></div> <img class="step-streetview" loading="lazy" src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mNkYAAAAAYAAjCB0C8AAAAASUVORK5CYII=" alt="Street view at step 2"> </div></li><li class="step step-heather-maybe"><span class="step-dir" title="Direction of travel">↙️</span> Continue onto C24 toward Solitaire <small>100 km · 1 hour 25 mins</small> <span class="step-heather-chip step-heather-chip-maybe" title="B1 paved trunk highway for the first ~90 km is comfortable. Hand the wheel at or before Rehoboth — the C24 gravel + Spreetshoogte Pass (14% gradient, 1,000 m drop in 4 km, no guardrails) is firmly David-only.">🟡 Heather: B1 Windhoek → Rehoboth only</span> <button class="step-expand" data-leg="0" data-step="2" aria-label="Expand step on map">🗺️</button><details class="step-conditions"> <summary class="step-conditions-summary"> <span class="step-road-pill">C24</span> <span class="step-conditions-toggle">conditions ▾</span> </summary> <div class="step-conditions-body"> <div class="step-road"><strong>Road:</strong> Gravel surface — usually well-graded but corrugated in stretches. Typical safe speed 60–80 km/h; loose surface lengthens braking distance ~2×.</div> <div class="step-rain"><strong>Rain:</strong> Rain: gravel becomes slick and potholes fill with water (hiding depth). Drop speed to 40–60 km/h. Avoid hard braking — let off-road reduce speed instead.</div> <div class="step-why"><strong>Heather rating:</strong> Heather maybe — gravel surface; she can manage short calm stretches but should hand back before corrugations or sharp turns. (Source note: B1 paved trunk highway for the first ~90 km is comfortable. Hand the wheel at or before Rehoboth — the C24 gravel + Spreetshoogte Pass (14% gradient, 1,000 m drop in 4 km, no guardrails) is firmly David-only.)</div> </div></details><div class="step-media"> <div class="step-map-osm" data-leg="0" data-step="2" data-status="maybe"></div> <img class="step-streetview" loading="lazy" src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mNkYAAAAAYAAjCB0C8AAAAASUVORK5CYII=" alt="Street view at step 3"> </div></li><li class="step step-heather-no"><span class="step-dir" title="Direction of travel">🏁</span> Arrive at Solitaire <small>1 km · 1 min</small> <span class="step-heather-chip step-heather-chip-no" title="David drives this portion — conditions or complexity make Heather unsuitable here.">🔴 David drives</span> <button class="step-expand" data-leg="0" data-step="3" aria-label="Expand step on map">🗺️</button><details class="step-conditions"> <summary class="step-conditions-summary"> <span class="step-road-pill">mixed</span> <span class="step-conditions-toggle">conditions ▾</span> </summary> <div class="step-conditions-body"> <div class="step-road"><strong>Road:</strong> Mixed local roads — surface and conditions vary segment to segment.</div> <div class="step-rain"><strong>Rain:</strong> Rain: check the worst surface type on this leg before deciding. Local advice from the lodge or Solitaire stop is the best signal.</div> <div class="step-why"><strong>Heather rating:</strong> David drives — route complexity, fatigue management, or unfamiliar intersections make this a David leg. (Source note: David drives this portion — conditions or complexity make Heather unsuitable here.)</div> </div></details><div class="step-media"> <div class="step-map-osm" data-leg="0" data-step="3" data-status="no"></div> <img class="step-streetview" loading="lazy" src="data:image/png;base64,iVBORw0KGgoAAAANSUhEUgAAAAEAAAABCAQAAAC1HAwCAAAAC0lEQVR42mNkYAAAAAYAAjCB0C8AAAAASUVORK5CYII=" alt="Street view at step 4"> </div></li></ol></div>"`;

